  "title": "Senior Electro-Mechanical Technician",
  "description": "<p>Reporting\nto the department owner, you will assist in the day-to-day operations and\nmaintenance of the Engineering Department to ensure all equipment is in good\ncondition in compliance with the highest safety and quality standards. </p><p><strong>Your\nKey Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Install, maintain, and repair machinery integrating\n     electrical and mechanical systems.  </li></ul><ul><li>Troubleshoot issues in electrical and mechanical\n     components.  </li></ul><ul><li>Perform preventive maintenance to ensure equipment\n     reliability and uptime.  </li></ul><ul><li>Read and interpret technical drawings, schematics, and\n     wiring diagrams.  </li></ul><ul><li>Follow all safety policies/procedures, GMPs, and\n     maintains an orderly and clean work area, Follow 5S standards.</li></ul><ul><li>Compliance with Group Quality Operational Requirements,\n     Group SHE Requirements, Quality Essentials, and Life Saving Rules (LSR).</li><li>Know how about Wastewater Treatment Plant Operation and\n     Boiler. Execute equipment troubleshooting and repair of static and\n     rotating equipment’s.</li><li>Leadership: Act as the backup for the respective shift.\n     Demonstrate ability to arrange daily maintenance schedule and coordinating\n     of resources. Coordinate with cross-functional teams as required to\n     ensure smooth operations and maintenance. Demonstrate the ability to\n     execute changes on the system, if needed (safety, quality rules,\n     equipment, 5S).</li></ul><p><strong>We\nOffer: </strong></p><ul><li><strong>Unique career paths across health, nutrition and beauty</strong> – explore what drives you and\n     get the support to make it happen. </li></ul><ul><li><strong>A chance to impact millions of consumers every day </strong>– sustainability\n     embedded in all we do. </li></ul><ul><li><strong>A science led company, cutting edge research and\n     creativity everywhere </strong>– from biotech breakthroughs to sustainability\n     game-changers, you’ll work on what’s next. </li></ul><ul><li><strong>Growth that keeps up with you</strong> – you join an industry leader\n     that will develop your expertise and leadership. </li></ul><ul><li><strong>A culture that lifts you up</strong> – with collaborative teams,\n     shared wins, and people who cheer each other on. </li></ul><ul><li><strong>A community where your voice matters</strong> – it is essential to serve our\n     customers well.  </li></ul><p><strong>You\nBring:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least Professional\n     Certificate/NITEC in Mechanical/Electrical or equivalent.  </li></ul><ul><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience in manufacturing\n     or production.  </li></ul><ul><li>Good attitude and willingness to learn.  </li></ul><ul><li>Effective verbal and written communication will be an\n     advantage.</li></ul><ul><li>Must be physically fit for heavy lifting of equipment\n     around 25KG.</li><li>This position will be on shift from 4pm - 12.30am,\n     Monday to Friday. Additional standby weekend support if required.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
